This is, of course, a love affair with LBJ, but there was a lot to love. A truly great man, and this is an homage to him. 
But even if you don't like LBJ, the historical artifacts are mind-boggling. 

So many original documents and items, that it is really an education. Like many museums, if you really want to read everything, it would take you an entire day. But you really want to budget between 2 and 3 hours. It closes at 5 p.m. and they chase you out of there right at 5. We got there at 4 and didn't really get a chance to explore the top floor at all. We just had an opportunity to run through it.  That floor is devoted to their life in the White House.

You will especially enjoy it if you lived  during this era, as it brings back so many memories. It is really beautifully done, and a must-see for a stay in Austin.

I'd never been to a presidential library and it is well worth the visit.  The architecture inside and out of this building is exquisite.  Very appealing to geometric lines and order.  It pretty formidable when you enter the main hall area.  the historical artifacts are expanse and it takes you through his tenure as VP and president, truly a historical experience.

make sure you venture to the floor containing a replica of the oval office.  even more inviting is ladybirds office.  It has spectacular view of Texas University stadium and downtown Austin.

LBJ leaves an incredible legacy which is well preserved in this wonderful archive. All stages of his life are documented in this fascinating collection. It was refreshing to see how much legislation LBJ was able to achieve during his presidency and to learn of his imposing presence. Lady Bird's life, the Vietnam war and a timeline of historical events are just a few highlights. I left a lot more educated about our amazing 36th president.

This is a Summertime go to when we have visitors in from out of town.  Don't get there too early...waiting and waiting until dusk can be tiresome.  I recommend bringing a blanket and watching from below or on the boardwalk w/ Transport Yourself Segway® Tours!!!

Holy bat cloud, Batman! This was a bucket list spot to visit for my son and I both. We had a blast watching the endless bats stream out from beneath the bridge at dusk. We love bats, and this is the most we have ever seen at once. I love how the local community has embraced these wonderful creatures and encourages others to appreciate them as well. Go watch the bats, you won't regret it. This made a great memory for us.

Had a great trip around the lake before the bats came out. Our captain got us right at and under the bridge as the show began it was crazy seeing that many bat at one time. Highly  recommend take the time to see it from the water.
Love coming here on the way back from San Antonio and watching the bats.

So we’ve been wanting to see the bats, but they were a no show. Now we did see and hear a few that flew over us. Talked to a local and he mentioned that May, June is best for a great view! So we’ll definitely make it back down there. Luckily The view was incredible!
Local venue, usually hosts plays. Essential to the performing community, it has decent parking and cool lights. Good place to see good theatre.
great local theatre

The University Library has an excellent atmosphere. It is quiet, serene and a great space for concentrating in your work. I spend hours in the Library, for my research work, and there remains no count of time. It is unbelievable that with quite a large demographic of students accumulating in that space, it is still silent and tranquil.

Over the years, the University of Texas at Austin has developed and built the campus into an increasingly beautiful place. There are innumerable study spots and incredible views to be found all over campus. Further, they've been working on street infrastructure to make campus walk-areas safer and more accessible to pedestrians or bikers. Overall, great university.

As a student at UT, all I have to say is that this school is the best. All staff and professors really care for everyone on campus. Also, safety for all is priority; UT police will come to the rescue soon. What starts at UT does changes the world.

Have had several visits here with my child who plans on attending soon.  LOVE the staff, hospitality and friendliness of all involved. First class school with a wonderful campus and a tremendous staff. Update, my daughter is attending UT now and LOVES it. Moooooove in day was a headache, however this school is really second to NONE!!!
Beautiful campus. Nice buildings. Seems safe.
Delicious, quality seafood! The prices are right too. This is a fabulous neighborhood resource!
Old and dingy but they have fresh and good quality produce.
My go to market for boiled crawfish(when in season) and fresh herbs and most anything else Asian produce related that I need.  Staff is friendly and knowledgeable about the products in stock.

This is a great market usual stop for jackfruit, bananas, Cassava other fruits and Veggies. Recently tried the the frozen soursop fruit $15, not worth it at all. The picture of that is tagged under this business. Anyways Found a better one at Walmart super center frozen section. Just the soursop pulp in a bag $3 & lot better taste. Still can’t beat what I’ve found in the Philippines 🇵🇭
It has most of the Asian groceries you need, good pricing, overall good.

Due to a mix up on my part with my landlord my water was shut off yesterday due to the land lord ending service. As a pet owner with two large dogs and a cat as well as a roommate I needed the water back on quickly. I went in, signed up and explained the situation and within 3 hours my water was back on. I realize this is definitely not the norm as far as turnaround time and truly appreciate the extra mile these folks went to help me.

While I do understand that sometimes water outages happen, my whole neighborhood has been without water over 17 hours (and counting!) with no explanation and no update as to how long it would take to fix.  There was no natural disaster or major reason why our water should be out this long.  Living without water in your house is a major deal and some update should be given to customers.  I asked to speak to the manager after I got no update from the customer service rep, but she said that because I wasn't the primary account holder (I rent), I wasn't able to.  So that's why I'm leaving a review.  Aqua Texas, you really need to change your policies and better serve your customers.

I had three of their pipes deteriorate and leak in my backyard. I had to spend several hours waiting for the contractors they hired to come and repair the pipes all three times and they left my yard lob sided from the dirt they didn't level.

I called Aqua regarding a water leak on their main, near my neighbors house. I first noticed the leak almost four months ago. I finally caught the neighbor at home about two months ago and they said it had been reported. Aqua sent someone out to paint a blue mark indicating where the leak is at. This leak is still ongoing, possibly contaminating the community water supply. The response from the Aqua emergency phone number was "Sir, you'll have to call back Monday after 9:00". Called back only to hear them say there was no report of a leak at the address, and there was no such address on Lakeridge  Loop. Tried to help this neighbor, but sorry, they're on their own now. It may get fixed after a meter reader falls through a sink hole caused by the leak.
If I could give them zero stars, I would. I was on hold for a supervisor for over 20 minutes and still never spoke to one. Worst customer service!

I'm so in love with Asia Cafe. There is nothing special to note about the atmosphere and that's not what Asia Cafe is about. It's about the delicious Chinese unique dishes and classic dishes they serve. The staff is so helpful and friendly. The food is very fresh, flavorful and prepared with great care. Sometimes they serve special items not on the regular menu so check out the boards where you place your order with the cashier. I strongly recommend any of the dumpling and steamed pork buns to start. Honestly, the food is great and be adventurous. Try a different dish each time, the food is delicious. Go here, give them a try. Their portions are large. I love this place for authentic Chinese dishes 💛

I lived in China for 4 years and got to have my fair share of Chinese food. After living there and going back for a visit in the States, the food definitely tasted authentic and delicious!! Some dishes are done better there than in China 😂 A great place to take groups of people to enjoy a good meal!

This is my favorite Chinese restaurant in all of Austin. It is very authentic and the food is so good. They go a little heavy on the oil sometimes so just as for light oil. The beef and broccoli is the best I've ever had. Their fried rice is legit too. This place is definitely worth your time. It is not super fancy but they have private rooms for family affairs. Enjoy!
Authentic Chinese food. With lots of variety. Staff are friendly explained about the dishes and service is fast during lunch.  We have enjoyed the food. Definatley recommend to try it.

We really love this place! We went last year on Dec. 31, 2018, and then also on this new year 2019 yesterday on the 1st of the year. Their food is excellent. If you are in Austin it is a must the are ranked #41 out of 50 Top Chinese Restaurant in the US. The portions are generous, the price is afortable, the taste is delicious.  We really enjoy going here as a family. The people are super nice and you have so many choices to choose from that you will not get bored if you went 3 or 4 times a week.

This place is so gross. The chicken wings, regardless of the flavor/sauce, taste so stomach-wrenching bad. Makes me sick. Plus, it’s pricey and parking was hard to find. I will never willingly go here and will offer 1000 alternatives to anyone who suggests we go to this restaurant to eat. Noisy, bad tasting, awful.

Pluckers was no disappointment.  My friends told me to go here.  I had an awesome time.  Vivian at the Bar was awesome and helped me order, literally I just trusted her with my choices.  With a full bar managing it alone, I was very happy with the service.

Hands down the best wing place. Their ranch will change your life, it’s become my new baseline. I always get the five wing combo with my fries tossed in bakers gold. The appetizers are all incredibly good and filling, love the fried pickles and holy Mac tossed in garlic parm.
This is the best place for hangout with your friends. I came so many time over here for celebrating our party. This bar has a great food quality and service is pretty good
Impossible burger was amazing! Staff was really nice!! Good drinks and good prices

Order right off the sidewalk !!  The burgers are tasty and the fries are crisp!!  Don't be afraid to ask for sauteed onions.  Staff is friendly and service is fast!  Great value.  Line moves quickly - it's worth the wait !

Are you kidding me! Who sells decent burgers and milkshakes at these prices. Got the double bacon burger and it was massive and very nice. Got the Oreo milkshake and it was good too.  I would pass on the peanut butter pretzels shake as it is grossly sweet and salty.  If they could calm down with the sugar...Nahhh it should be taken off menu.

Like the booth style and if I want burgers in Austin then I will be back!

They also have this cool little mayo fridge with all these crazy flavour options. Was impressed with the effort but does not work.

The area is great and will make you want to come back. If you're looking for a clean place, a well-groomed and well-lit areas, amazing food then this is a place for you. I recommend coming here if you want to. It's a great place to relax and unwind and just get away with a good burger. Again I do recommend coming here.

Great burger, fair price. Don't miss out on the queso fries. When we go, it's usually Sunday afternoon after walking the lake or strolling around downtown.  I'm sure the experience is much different at night but it's very relaxed on Fun Day. 

It's a great place to grab a quick bite while sitting outside, enjoying the weather and people watching on Congress. 

I've been meaning to try other burgers but I keep going back to the bacon burger. It's a standard that's hard to resist.

Nothing really special. Felt like just an overpriced burger because of convenience and downtown. If you provide it they will come. The fries had no flavor but oil and if you drenched them in ketchup. The soda was canned and if you don't drink it fast it'll get warm quick. So for the combo that is over $9...I'll stick to Sandy's or Whataburger.

Great food and service in a casual atmosphere. 
And I can't say enough good things about their people!  The ownership and staff are amazing.  They host our alumni events and bend over backwards to accommodate our group.  Love the Waterloo peeps

Had the catfish platter with slaw and mashed potatoes. Great as always!  The fish was fried darker than I liked but still tasted great.  Everything was great and the staff was nice but one word of advice:  when someone just spent $48.00 on 2 platters and tea it would be very considerate if you’d tell the customer “bye” or “comeback soon” or something.  Just saying
As usual, staff and food were AWESOME!  Seth made this most recent visit very memorable!  Thanks for making us feel the love!
Fried chicken was good and came with good sides(I choose Mac& Cheese with Chives and Bacon bits and another side of Mashed potatoes. Definitely filled me up. Sweet tea is fair
Waterloo never disappoints. The food is great and the service is always top notch. They make you feel like home.

This place is AMAZING. I ordered the bacon cheeseburger, fries, fresh lemonade and a Root beer milkshake. Everything was outstanding and at a good price. Since it was all organic stuff I figured it would be expensive. It's a cool little place with outdoor seating. At night they have lights strung up overhead.

Delicious simple burgers with great toppings. They even have a veggie burger which is pretty good. This location with 2 windows is fantastic and very fast to get the food out. The lemonade itself is worth driving here for!
Austin burger icon. Fresh burgers, cut fries and shakes. Drive thru at this location. Low cost. Good late(r) night spot. Shakes worth the extra stop. Quick in and out. Service is very friendly.
Excellent burgers, fries. And fresh squeezed lemonade! Love that they use natural and fresh ingredients. We will for sure be back!
Recommended by a local.  We've been there three times in 10 days.  Fresh burgers, real fries recognizable as coming from actual potatoes.  I am very fond of their buns.

This place is so well design. I must confess I hate the concept a little. The whole stand in line for infinite hours to maybe get what you went for. But, at the same time is one of the many ways it makes this place so special and also doesn't pair with a regular food chain, because it's not. Food is always amazing, personnel is amazing, people there in general are amazing. We honestly go to Austin just to eat here.

This place was recommended by a friend who had visited Austin, he warned me the line would form quickly and early in the morning. That was the absolute truth! I arrived at 9 am and was able to make it to the counter to order my scrumptious BBQ at Noon, yes you read that correctly Noon! Don’t fret though, you will not be disappointed. This is some of the best BBQ I have ever had. The owner is so friendly and hands out samples of the amazing brisket before you order. Wow, just wow!!! I never thought I would say I stood in line for 3 hours for BBQ, but I did. I am so glad I took my friends recommendation and tried Franklin’s BBQ! Yummy!!!!!

Franklin is quite an experience. First there’s the line ( during the week they start cueing up as early as 5:30 AM) make sure you get there by 7:30 AM. Bring a chair and a thermos of your favorite brew, some bring coolers with a different brew. I suggest a light breakfast as the doors open by 11:00 AM it will still take at least an hour before you  get your food. Make sure you eat there as well for the total effect. As you reach the carving station the excitement builds. Watching the carving process and the interaction with the servers is truly entertaining. You are treated with the utmost care and consideration. All the employees are courteous and friendly . Don’t forget to purchase some swag so you can proudly fly the Franklin flag. Now the meats, brisket is beyond explication, heavenly perfection. The pork ribs are the best I’ve ever had, tender fall off the bone , and precision smoked. The beef rib (Saturday only) is a must just for the sheer size of it! Turkey is juicy and flavorful, and the sausages were good as well. Try the deserts as the Lemon pie and pecan pie where awesome!

There is no better smoked beef brisket anywhere. Consistently the best there is. Cooked slowly with all-wood smoke. The absolute pinnacle of central Texas barbecue. If you like smoked brisket, this is what it should taste like.  Waiting in line is an international tailgate party every time.
The 2-5 hour line is crazy. But WELL worth the wait. Absolutely phenomenal food. The sauces only get a 3/5 but the meat doesn't even need it. Melt in your mouth brisket is the American dream.

Food and drinks were delicious. It was unlike other Mexican food I've ever had. I'm not sure if it was more authentic but certainly not your usual Tex-Mex. Our mango margaritas appeared to be fresh fruit. The service and atmosphere were just okay. I would definitely come back for the food.

Went there at midnight. They were closing down but still served us tacos. We ordered two pork and one steak, on corn tortillas, and got three steak on flour tortillas. The steak was tough and had a strong soy taste, almost like a Chinese restaurant. Wouldn’t go back during off hours again.

Polvo's is one of the recommended Mexican cuisine restaurants in Austin.  Great Austin atmosphere and wonderful food with an interior Mexico lean.  Best sauce bar in Austin.  Very busy at peak times and parking a bit limited but well worth it.

Love this place. good food and good drinks. Margaritas are delicious. staff is friendly. I've never had a bad experience. Fun place to meet with friends. Parking is a bit tight and sometimes this place can get crowded.

The food, service, and patio were excellent! Ordered a pitcher of margaritas, beef fajitas, and chili con queso. I left very full and happy, with a small box of leftovers. Thank you! I will be back soon!

Seriously love this place! Every time I visit Austin, it’s a must! The avocado margarita is to die for and the salsa is divine. The veggie tacos are great, so fresh and flavorful. The staff is always really nice and friendly. Great service and even better food, what more can you ask for?

I love Curra's because it is a hidden gem amongst a sea of Tex-Mex in Austin. Curra's is as authentic to actual Mexican cuisine as you can get. I highly recommend the tamales and the avocado margarita. The tamales are the biggest I've seen in Austin, and are always hot, fresh and moist. Their borracha sauce is SO good! This place is always busy, but the service is kind of slow. If you're not in a rush, you'll be fine, but expect to sit for about 7 minutes before anyone asks about your beverage order. Despite this, I still come here regularly. The food is worth it!

food is great most of the time.  had slow service  this trip but that is because 1 waiter was assigned to the whole outside.  love that i can bring my dog on patio through the dog door.  the food this trip was not so good.  overkill on the green sauce.   weekends have white rice however the rice tasted like fish.  the Raspberry marg was phenomenal.

Omg that food was truly incredible! And the portions were so large, we each had a meal for the next day. The salsa was fresh and had a.yummy roasted flavor, can't wait to try the salsa sampler next time. 10/10 would recommend!

Great food and atmosphere. I've visited a couple of times now. Had the nachos with shrimp one time, very delicious! Good selection of beer and drinks. The Summer Twister is delicious, but a tad expensive ($9.50), more than what I like to pay for a mixed drink but still a yummy drink. Parking can be a bit tight at times. Great service. Price points for food are good.

Drinks are delicious.  Puffy tacos are outstanding.  Must have been an off night, because our server was distracted.  But other wait staff were more than accommodating to our needs.  Enchiladas were very good too.  You really can't go wrong here.

I used to go to Baby A’s all the time and I was sad to learn that the I-35 location closed. I hadn’t been to a Baby A’s in a long time. I went with my girlfriend and the service was amazing. Management was always checking on everybody. Waiters and waitresses were quick and attentive. They were always moving and my drink was never empty. The food was amazing and the drinks are great too! I love the atomosphere and I will definitely be returning here to have some more great times. Money well spent and like I said, I will be returning. Keep up the good work.

Yum yum Mexican food!!!  I love this place and it is a notch above many other Mexican places.  

First off the salsa is so good. It’s spicy, garlicky and you can’t stop eating it. I dipped everything I could in that little salsa bowl and yes it was good. 

The baby A soup is tasty as any other tortilla soup would taste like. Except it has a lot more chicken, tender shredded chicken topped off with a slice of avocado. I like it, warms me right up today. 

The second half of the soup combo is a nice healthy side of Spanish rice with a taco. I picked puffy taco with chicken. It’s good but the puffy taco is little dense than I like. But all and all it is still good. 

Happy eating.

This is a really cool place to drink PURPLE MARGARITAS! The staff is friendly, food is really really good! But what made me write a review was Miguel’s customer service. He was attentive, and actually had a personality. Unlike infamous restaurants in Austin who have good food but terrible service or robot servers/waitress. Thank you Miguel for making me and my husband’s day!
Oily bowls, the cocktails were too sugary and not at all refreshing. Seemed like gross chain-restaurant food. Staff was nice though. Edit: my wife got the tortilla soup and it was very good!

This is the third or fourth time I've been to Maudie's and now I feel qualified to do a review. Service is generally very good. The menu is beautifully colorful. The chips and salsa are very good. Iced tea is good and they use great ice. The food has been a struggle for me. I've tried the Al Pastor tacos and the  Carnitas Burrito lately and I would not order either again. The rice and beans were bland. My friend had enchiladas and seemed to be pleased. I will try them next time and maybe they will be the menu item that brings me back. Their bar and happy hour are generally great and may just be the best thing about the restaurant. That's what keeps me coming back.

Excellent. Appetizer was queso n chips. Not heavy, great starter. Bowl w/fajita meat was spot on. Service was smooth, timely delivery on orders. It's cozy and simple restaurant with great atmosphere.  Tex-Mex done right👍
Our server was very attentive, even though we were in the corner of the restaurant. The service was quick and the food was delicious. Would recommend!

The food and drinks aren't the best, but the service more than makes up for it. It's the perfect place to bring toddlers as the place is filled with other families and your little one will not go without. I will say that the cheese enchiladas are excellent.
Very quick service at this location. I almost always choose between the power bowl or the beef fajita enchiladas with queso on top.

Best Breakfast Tacos in Austin!!
Taco Express is the best - no doubt about it. Their breakfast is awesome, that I've never made it to the lunch menu no matter what time of day I go there. They serve breakfast all day! Perfect for those weekend days that you wake up later than normal. They have a different vibe in their dining room, it's very Austin. Great food and service. The salsa is terrific also. Their tacos are super tasty, not overly greasy and they give you a lot inside their tacos, they are pretty full. Their location is fairly easy to get to and they take phone orders and are super speedy!

Maria's is an Austin classic. With a menu that will satisfy any diet or craving. Their in house corn tortillas are the best I've ever had. They are dog friendly and have amazing music on Sundays. If you're in Austin, and you want good tacos hit up Maria's.

The food here was so delicious. Everything was made fresh to order. Food was ready quickly and people were cleaning the entire time we were there. Great variety of food choices. Lots of personality. There was outdoor seating as well as an upstairs lounge. I would love to visit again the next time I'm in town.

Pretty cool place. Went to play Big Boobied Bingo there one Tuesday night and had a good time. Their queso is alright, i think everything there is pretty much frozen then heated. Margaritas was good though. Not too sure about their food yet.

Went for Big Boobie Bingo while visiting Austin - had a BLAST! The hosts were hysterical and kept us laughing for 3 hours. We had the chips and queso (delicious), and our friends had tacos - they looked really good. The drinks (margaritas, full bar, soda, etc) were hand crafted and reasonably priced. Get there early for a good seat.

Garrido's has a beautiful, central location right on a creek full of greenery, which makes for an idyllic atmosphere. The staff is friendly and the happy hour prices are great. But the main draw is the creative Mexican fusion menu. Tex-Mex and even some Hawaiian flavors going on. Good stuff!

Garrido's is a compact, well-decorated and cool venue to sample some of the better modern Mexican cuisine in Austin. The 3 course brunch is popular at weekends and the Happy Hour drinks and appetizer specials are a hit any day of the the week. While service can slow down during busy periods, you won't necessarily care if you get seated on the patio in temperate weather. Don't miss the margaritas and don't be afraid to speak up if you're vegetarian or vegan since the kitchen seems to accommodate these off-menu requests easily.

Creative Mexican cuisine in a bright and airy setting, with a patio overlooking a wooded stretch of Shoal Creek. The food is very good; the margaritas are divine. We've come here for a meal on occasion, but are more likely to stop by the bar for a few drinks and appetizers during happy hour.

Food is good, but the portion size is really small. Had a groupon and went on Monday night (happy hour all night), so managed to get a good meal without breaking the bank. Spent only $35, which was a great deal. Without the discounts though, the meal would have been almost $100. And that was for 2 people with only one margarita each. The nacho apps are four individual chips for $10! It was good, but not that good. Worth maybe $5, and that's stretching it!

I came here not expecting much, as there are so many amazing restaurants in Austin and you kind of figure that 'well, if I haven't heard of it by now it's probably no big deal.' I was dead wrong with this place. First of all, the corn tortillas are hand-made and so good that they make me actually like corn tortillas. The drinks were delicious and the coffee marinated steak tacos changed my whole feeling about tacos. The fish tacos were the only thing that even compared to the rest and a great starting point for my feast. The outdoor patio was all lit up with lights for the holidays and a band plays on Friday nights to set the mood. I will definitely be back.

A group of us chooses a different restaurant each month to try. We love trying new places and try to give objective reviews. We visited Serrano's on Sat, March 23 for dinner (7 p.m.). I made reservations, however, it's a large restaurant so I'm sure they take walk-ins. 

Pros:
*Upon arrival, I was seated immediately (didn't need entire group to be seated like in some restaurants). 
*Good location, easy to find.
*The drinks were delicious.
*Server was knowledgeable about the drink menu.
*Food arrived quickly, and hot.
*Good for large groups.
*Plenty of parking space

To be improved:
*The server was a bit slow and forgetful. I ordered salt on the rim of my drink, it came with none. He was going to get me some, I never received it. My friend wanted to take a pic of the bottle of the liqueur used in his drink, the server offered to get it but forgot to bring it. 
*Overall, three of four people in the group rated the food bland. The chips and salsa were good, however, the salsa was very spicy (no other options available-I think this is a Texas thing). Another server offered to ask the cook if he could make some less spicy. I declined but appreciated the offer.
*Female bathroom is like an ice box.
*When leaving, the hostess was at the counter with her head down, like she was tired, bored or hungover. Shows poor management of the place.

Not bad.  Not a complaint.  It truly wasn't bad.  3 stars is better than average.  4-5 is reserved for over the top imho.  Mexican food is so subjective.  My 4-5 range might be your 1-2.  I do recommend this place. Service is good.  It's clean.
Best staff and always very attentive. The food is good but some reason the south park meadows location has more flavor... but nevertheless this location is amazing and ALWAYS taste great!
Serrano's is definitely a favorite. Food is always good and our friend Gustavo is always close by with an extra basket of chips. The Emcie with fresh onions on the enchilada is where it's at.

This is great place for a quick breakfast/brunch. The food is great, cheap, and fast. We have never had to wait here! There are so many places that have crazy waits. This place is dependable and the service is great.

I loved the tamale! It was my very first time eating it and I loved them so much. The fish tacos was so fresh too, and the pork was great. I also enjoyed a wonderful margarita in such a lovely atmosphere. Cannot believe how friendly everyone was with us too, super hospital.

Authentic Mexican food and amazing tamales. 2nd generation owner operated. Proud family recipes. Extra bonus was there is a women's vintage and super affordable boutique with great light wear fashions at a great value! Great time.

Some of the best tamales I've had in Austin with great prices for many options in east Austin. The margaritas are pre-mixed which is likely due to the volume they need to accommodate for. 

The decor is wonderful and there is a great outdoor seating area. I'll definitely be visiting again.
Excellent food. Not Tex-Mex, real Mex. Moles were awesome, but if you don't know what you want, just have them pick for you. It's all good food.
Loved my first experience!  The food was delicious- SO flavorful!  The band was fantastic and the dancing was super fun!  Great, fun and laid back atmosphere!

Pretty decent. Lunch is come and seat yourself. The Mexican martini is what we got and is pretty decent in size. Service is a wee bit slow but still kind and caring. I understand when you only have one server for a busy lunch, they get busy but I never felt neglected. A decent place
Food was great and the martini margarita was a GREAT value!  It was a little noisy so it was hard to hold an intimate conversation. All in all, great place I have been going to for over 20 years

Mexican Martinis are #1 
Staff are always the best! No negative things to write about this restaurant or location! Keep up the outstanding work!

I love this place.  I am not sure how they manage to employ a staff that is so profession and polite.  They must have really good training. Great bar and awesome food.  Key take away... they are a late night gem that serves food well past midnight... and that is a really short list.
Best location by far. Bar area is easier to get a table fast but main restaurant is way nicer. Migas, stuffed avocado, and chicken fried steak are delicious and portions are generous.

It's like the amusement park of Italian food! My friends + I love coming here. The food is amazing! We've never been disappointed. And the desserts are something to write home about. Take a coffee to-go because it doesn't disappoint either 😋😋

Before I get to praising the fantastic family-friendly ambiance and excellent food (which plenty other reviewers already have done), I want to say a great big thank you for one of the nicest and the most thoughtful changing table/accommodation I've seen anywhere in public, let alone in the men's room no less. I feel that there will be other fathers of young children who will certainly appreciate this. 

This was my first visit and even before food came out, I felt instantly welcomed as a guest. Food was as great as I thought it would be. I didn't get the gelato this time, but most certainly will for future visits.
I always eat here when I'm in town they have delicious food. I have never had a bad experience since I have started going and it's going on  6 years. Definitely a good place to try Italian foods!

Mandola's has wonderful Italian food with fast and friendly service. I love their Fettuccine Alfredo! They are centrally located in the Triangle and also have a deli and dessert section in their restaurant. Awesome spot!

We ordered a 12 inch Italian sausage, pepperoni and mushrooms. The pizza had good flavor but you could not pick up a slice with one hand, too soft. Not to mention hands got very greasy every time you picked it up. They bring you a basket of some great Italian pan bread and a great dipping sauce. We also ordered some garlic bread with cheese. Very good Italian bread. Looking a the pictures along with the reviews on Google one might think they bake a bunch of different types of Italian bread and display them in the baskets for sale. That is not the case. A manager told me that those are old pictures on Google. Also note there isn't any salad bar. Might look like it in the pictures. The employees working the floor were very friendly. The ones behind the counter a little smug. Several options for seating inside or outside. It's a little confusing how you get started. There is a sign that says; wait to be seated but, you need to go to the counter to order your meal and than they will bring it to your table. The atmosphere was a little mundane for an Italian restaurant but they did have a lot of pictures on the wall covering their history. The pizza, garlic bread with cheese, 2 salads and 2 drinks $34 with tax. Very reasonable. There is also a display with Italian ice cream and several baked desserts. All and all we think you will enjoy it also. We would return if we lived in Austin.

This was my birthday dinner.   I chose something out  of my comfort zone.  I am glad I did.  The dining area was fresh and easy to get along with.  The food was exceptional. The beverage was delightful. The combination worked well. Well worth it! It’s a dining pleasure.

There is a reason this place is packed on a Thursday night at 10pm. Some the best food I have ever had! The service is like your visiting an old friend who was nothing but nice to you. The chef has some really interesting ideas when it comes to raw fish and Japanese cuisine, setting this place apart from the others.

Seriously the best dining experience I've ever had. The service (our waitress Jodi was amazing,) the food, and the atmosphere was top notch. I've never had food as delicious as this was and I've never had a service run so smoothly from waitstaff. Everyone that brought food to us knew exactly what was in the dish and they were all aware of a peanut allergy one of us had. I would HIGHLY recommend Uchi to anyone who is feeling  adventurous and looking for a great meal. 12/10 would eat again.
Outstanding sushi restaurant, one of the best in the country, let alone Texas. Creative and innovative dishes. Great ambiance, great service. Definitely need reservations.
Best place in Austin to have sushi. Charming upscale Austin style restaurant. Reservations are highly recommended and it's not child friendly in terms of food.

Best ice cream ever! An Austin classic! Very fun and funky vibes. I've been here dozens of times and loved every visit. Great service and super tasty ice cream with loads of choices! Their Mexican vanilla is a classic.

Very disappointed! May look fun and inviting from the outside, but no, it’s a tourist trap for the following reasons: only about 15 ice cream flavors total (most other homemade ice cream shops typically have 30+), ice cream itself when served was almost half melted in all honesty (never had such melted ice cream served before probably because they mixed in M&Ms on a warm table before serving), and overall the flavor of the ice cream was not that great (thin mint tasted like vanilla with crushed thin mint cookie). Importantly, the serving sizes are so small - tiny, small and large sizes are about 1/2 cup, cup and 1.5 cups for $4,$5, and $6, respectively. Not impressed :/

Great variety of desserts at Amy's Ice Creams. If you are in town i recommend stop by here, grab yourself a small ice cream and enjoy it while walking along S Congress. Also, from time to time they'll have Amy's mugs that you can keep as a souvenir.
I had a very good dark chocolate ice cream with a little bit sea salt on it. Definitely recommend!

For waiting well over 30 minutes, the ice cream just wasn't worth it. Hardly any flavor at all in the chocolate cheesecake. Brownies tasted like dried stale chocolate crumbles. Mexican vanilla was tasty, but overall experience brings this down to just 2 stars. Not worth the long wait.

I'd give it 4.5 stars if I could. I really enjoyed this place, the decor screamed post-shift bar without the seediness. It was cozy, the food didn't break the bank and I'll be damned if it wasn't good. But, alas it was bar food, and if you were looking for something more complex then you may want to consider other options. In short, it was good and not terribly priced. It was comfortable. Does it try and be what it's not? No. And that's just fine.  Almost five stars, just not quite.

Went out with coworkers. The outside seating was cozy and nice, despite being next to a freeway and a viewing area of the malls. Wine selection is good and the beer selection even more so. Food is actually better than expected for being bar food. Service was prompt and informative.
I only give 4/5 stars because of the traffic and speed bumps you have to negotiate.  The food is always great with little wait time.  My favorite is the Cuban sandwich with sweet potato fries.

The server was awesome. The ambiance was fine. They were welcoming and friendly when I arrived.

We were there with a HUGE group with the back room reserved, the staff was buzzing constantly trying to meet our needs. A few balls got dropped,
though like my friends drink orders and food orders were forgotten entirely at one point, but we finally managed to get it taken care of. 

At the end of the night, they let us stragglers chat and sip our beers while they were cleaning up. However the private room was not protected from the noise of the main bar, and their promised amenities were not communicated to the staff and necessary cabeling to make use of the big screen was neither available not communicated to us in advance so we could have provided our own.  Not planning to return for a private event. I am sure we would have payed less to order our own food and drinks and occupied the same space as an impromptu large group.

Sat outside. Did not receive menu for 15 mins. Got the wrong fries we ordered (and charged for them), fried pickles were really salty, asked for ketchup (or any sauce they have) to go with fries - didn't see any for entire time we were there. Imagine eating fries just by themselves. Ordered wings which never even saw the cook's eyes. We were told they forgot about it, when we were waiting for them for half hour already. Just paid and left. We used to love coming here but the service is getting worse.

As much as it pains me to write this, this location has taken a serious dive since the Amazon takeover. I've been going here a few times a week for an eternity and it's depressing to watch the negative trend. 
1. The PEOPLE. Staff is universally lower quality. From the bearded gentleman working meat without a hairnet to the guy with gold glasses working hot food that hates his job, I see daily examples that employees are no longer the cheery, environmentally conscious type and are now just any retail employees that would take any job. They're not all bad - - the vets in seafood are awesome - - but it's noticeable every time I visit. 

2. The PRICING games are tiring. "we're slashing prices!" *weeks later * "just kidding, here's 10% off for sale items, but all prices have been silently raised by 20%!" it seems like my bill has steadily crept up for the past year as some nerd with an algorithm tests price elasticity.

3. They've increased the amount of self serve hot bar items while decreasing the amount of employees serving the reasonably priced hot vegetables. I frequently find myself trying to track down an employee, waiting for new batches of veggies, or waiting in a long line. To boot, the hot food quality is lower across the board. Veggies come out without seasoning sometimes.

I love Amazon, but I miss the old Whole Foods.

We go here on a regular basis! Service is great and staff is always friendly and willing to help. The coffee bar is terrific. They make anything you like with vegan milk options. The hot food bar is always fresh and clean. They also have vegan options in their big and small individual bakery sections. They make fresh custom juices here which are a bit pricey but delicious.

WOW! I have never been in a supermarket this fancy before. They’ve got a full on pub and stuff, what supermarket has that! Of course the stuff is a bit more pricey, but the stuff does look amazingly better! If I do get a chance to come here again I absolutely will. You don’t even have to buy anything, just come here and experience it.

We are life long customers of Whole Foods in Austin and, for the most part, we enjoy shopping there. Unfortunately, sometimes, our shopping experience is not optimum. Namely, on a recent visit, we noticed that there was a new surcharge for buying half a loaf of bread, instead of the usual half price for half the loaf. When we inquired if this was a mistake the associate there told us that "this was a new policy that came straight down from corporate", obviously, herself, not happy with it. We hope that this was a one-time mistake that corporate made since Whole Foods has prided itself in being a full service grocery store, charging a premium for their products (the type of bread we bought is priced at 30% more at Whole Foods than the equivalent product at Central Market) and not start nickel-and-dimeing their customers like some cheap convenience stores do.

This place is awesome! They have a huge selection of healthy foods. They're a little pricey but very worth it. About a week after buying groceries here, I just had a lot more energy and felt all around better. There are a bunch of little food shops inside too. I've never had a bad experience here. If you're looking to save money, it's worthwhile to download the Whole Foods Market app. It automatically applies any coupons that are available to your cart! Plus, the in-house 365 brand prices are comprable to HEB.
Truly excellent! Wonderful friendly staff, great atmosphere, great food. Will most certainly make this a regular haunt.
Their fogs are worth the trip to Austin!! Will be visiting again soon!
Everyone should eat here... never would know it's geared towards vegetarian and vegan food. Everything is delicious.... funky atmosphere and great service too!

reviews.author_name: East Austin Realty Expert - Scott Cooper Smith
reviews.text: A very hip spot in a very hip town.
Bouldin Creek coffee house is the same as bouldin Creek cafe... Not sure why there are two...I have even walked in an asked and was told.by the host at bouldin Creek cafe they are the same

Imagine eating fries just by themselves. Ordered wings which never even saw the cook's eyes. We were told they forgot about it, when we were waiting for them for half hour already. Just paid and left. We used to love coming here but the service is getting worse.

This has become one of my favorite spots after just two visits. I went for dinner the first time and fell in love with the grit tots and biscuits with honey butter. Amazing start to my meal and the shrimp and grits entree was also incredible. My fiancé had steak which was also very well prepared and juicy. Second time we had brunch and it was amazing! The chicken and waffles were a generous portion with a delicious hot sauce. The French toast had great texture and flavor. I would highly recommend the biscuits and grit tots, must try if you dine here.

This place is assume and the food is great. A nice spin on the hot sauce. I had the shrimp and grits nice size shrimps and grits soft and the seasoning great. I'm from Charleston SC, so I know what good food taste like. 
I could go on and on but you gotta go there and see for yourself.

Have had brunch here twice, both times were excellent. After a night of partying, its hard to beat chicken n waffles with a mimosa. The biscuits are always warm out of the oven, and the gravy was pretty good. The chicken & waffles is a great deal for under $20, its a ton of food that will set you on a path to Deep Couch City. I am salivating just thinking about it.

All of the food was fresh, creative, flavorful and delicious.  The cocktails we're excellent as well.  It has a rustic farmhouse vibe which compliments the southern themed menu.  The atmosphere was lively and energetic and the bar has a unique design with a decent amount of seating.

Go for a good brunch experience. Great food and soothing ambience. 
Must try— Short rib hash and biscuits.
Bumin Kim art.= Cruz-Diez meets Gabrial Dawe.

Last night The Incredible Red Dot Fundraising Event for Women and Their Work beckoned. It turned out to be a truly  amazing gathering of local artists, art collectors, and unique pieces of art. As the evening wore on, it quickly became slithering room only as patrons of the arts made their purchases or bid on silent auction donations. Tiny red dots began appearing to indicate pieces no longer available. Food by Locavore, Home Slice, and drinks featuring Titos, and local wine rounded out a spectacular evening for the arts in Austin, Texas! Director Rachel Stuckey is clearly putting her talent and artistry to amazing use!
Rare and unique art Gallery! Must see in ATX
Great gallery with really friendly staff!
Wonderful art. Wonderful people. Wonderful place.

Loved the burger...the meat so fresh and tasty. The buffalo burger with blue cheese is so good that you can't stop eating. Fries texture can be enhanced. The fries dip is really good, you can request it from them. 
As for the atmosphere it is amazing! Very Texan style. Rock music, rock style men & women. This is a very unique place & a must visit in Austin.

HANDS DOWN!!! BEST BURGER PLACE EVER!!! I've been coming here since 1997 and it never disappoints. The burgers are amazing. A few things to remember if your ordering food(remember....no soup for you!) Look at the menu and know what you want PRIOR to getting to the window. Have cash to cover plus a cash tip. Make sure the cook sees you put the tip in the jar. Wait your 45-90 minutes and enjoy!!!

This place has some really great burgers. Patties are thick a flavorful. We've been coming here for years since seeing them on triple d. Wings are very good as well. Good beer selection, great juke box, we'll keep coming back.

Chill bar on dirty sixth with hearty burgers and sides. Chili drys were a meal on their own, heavy portion! The burgers are fresh cooked and huge. Chill alternative vibe, great to have a bite to eat or grab a drink.

Kind of a unique place. You yell your order in a window and chill out til its ready.  I had the KC burger it was good but I will have to say  the burger was undercooked but it might have been because it was really a thick burger. The atmosphere is part From Dusk til Dawn bar to custom built burger joint. If you're on dirty 6th street pop in you wont be sorry.

Searched the area for a highly rated low-key pizza place and this had great reviews and the pictures looked delicious! Uber picked us up and dropped us off...the place was closed! The sign on the door had the hours posted that matched with Google maps, but the lights were out and no sign as to why they were closed. Sorry I missed out....
pizza... excellent. great spot for an appetite of any size. the place has a nice atmosphere. i see why this place has so many great reviews.
Ordered BBQ and chicken pizza, only tasted sauce and nothing else. place could use a face lift after 10 plus years. doubt we'd return.
Sadly, they are closed down for good.  Great downtown eatery
A great pizza joint. Good atmosphere. Workers are friendly . Good flavor in food. And good prices.

Been savoring everything they serve since I got to Austin in 1966. Seems like Everytime is better than the last. This mushroom burger took me to gustatory heights of rapture I can't even describe. And the onion rings were as usual REAL and delicious.

This is just the sort of review I hate to write. Hut’s has a plethora of very positive reviews, a devoted following and a menu that is mouthwatering. As we walked in, we could see delicious appearing burgers and onion rings on many tables. But the burger we had was overcooked, flavorless and had an almost gritty texture. The buns were of no particular note and the onion rings, tho’ they were gorgeous to behold, had no flavor whatsoever. When I have a great onion ring (like at a top flight steak house) the last thing I want is ketchup. Here, the first thing I went for was the ketchup. Despite the hype and great service, Hut’s was a major disappointment. My wife said she’d give it a “1”, but I’m writing the review, so they get a “2”.
Good burgers. Decent Fries. Fun atmosphere. Parking is tight. Quick service. Ketchup bottles a bit sticky.

Huts. The original, the iconic, an Austin institution. Lots on the menu, but it's all about the hamburgers. 20 different ways. By the way, don't miss  the number 20 burger, its the classic. The fries are great too. They say the chicken fried  steak is great, but can never NOT have the burger. Funky Austin weird decor. It's a must stop if you come to Austin. Don't miss it. If you want health food, you can go to Whole Foods. This is about Good food

The only good thing about this place is the meat on the burgers is truly delicious. However everything else is horrible. The fries are bad the onion rings are gross, the malts were tiny. Everything was super overpriced, for the quantity. The waiter we had was moody and rude and hardly refilled our drinks. Terrible experience; don’t know why this place got such great reviews. Your better off not going here!

A hidden gem of Austin. Thus place has great portion sizes for ten bucks or less. The amount of complimentary items was astounding. The service was on point and the staff was genuinely personable and funny. The building is small and cozy, which I like. Every Austinite should try this place, but they're so small and quiet that I'm surprised I found them at all.
Fresh and delicious ingredients.  Consistently great food.  Awesome service.  Love coming here for lunch!

Possibly my new favorite place in Austin, the food was incredible and the staff exceeded expectations. I had the Koriente Curry (A) and added broccoli and spicy chicken (they comped the broccoli just as a nice gesture). I also ordered bubble tea which was great because it was the first I had had in a long time that wasn't too sweet. I also enjoyed the complimentary miso soup (vegan, salt free) while we waited for food (which only took about 10 minutes). Intimate atmosphere with friendly staff. Be weary of parking though!

Never had the food here but the teas are amazing! Small little spot but there is always a line out the door so that has to be a good sign right?! The owner is really cool and is very passionate about everything they do there!
A preferred scene for delicious Asian food. The food was so savory. The service was very welcoming and sociable. It has an awesome feel to it. This place has many good reviews for a reason.

Good food great service attached to a very nice Best Western Plus hotel. Being a seasoned traveler for work, this was one of the best hotels for being known as a "budget friendly" chain. Opal had a very nice selection of all liquors, with signature cocktails and a selection of craft beers. Very clean which is comforting when eating out.

Beautiful new location. The restaurant is beautiful. I would recommend you have your back of house employees be a little more quiet or watch profanities. Chicken fried steak had a wonderful flavor and the hatch chillies were delicious. The portion seemed like a lunch portion and a bit over cooked. All in all I think it was a good experience. I would definitely be back.
Great food and good service. Even though my server was new, she was attentive and super friendly. Will definitely come back again when I am in Texas again.
Another great true treasure of Austin. I recommend the chicken fried steak and great close but far atmosphere.

Didn't expect too much out of a restaurant attached to a best Western, but was pleasantly surprised. The food is by no means top tier, but it was very good and high quality sports bar style food. Drinks are very inexpensive and there's an excellent variety of options (three mezcal options?! Unheard of). Prices for a mezcal margarita and food for two was only $35. Awesome.

Favorite place to grab a bite + drinks when my sister and I visit Austin. Awesome staff and service. Even better food! Prices are cheap and drinks are strong, definitely getting the bang for your buck here! Lively, comfortable, and cool atmosphere.

I really liked the chili. I got the 3 chili sample meal. All were delicious. There are several other things on the menu that I'd love to try. Everyone else in my group loves the food too.
The place was packed, and the service was just alright, which is the only reason I wouldn't give it five stars.

A hole in the wall place near the Texas Capitol. I loved all the signs and memorabilia splashed on the walls. As a first timer I had the medium spice chili which was perfect even though I like spicy foods. It's a little pricey for the portions though.

Kind of dive place but the Chili was really good.  The guacamole was delicious.  The breakfast steak and scramble was really good. The prices are good as well. It's worth a visit if you're looking for something different in downtown Austin.
This was my first time coming here, I had a wonderful time. I ordered a loaded chili potatoes.  It was huge and the staff were nice. Definitely going back again!
Local venue, usually hosts plays. Essential to the performing community, it has decent parking and cool lights. Good place to see good theatre.
great local theatre

This is my third time here. My father and I went for breakfast around 10am on a Saturday. There was a good number of people. There was no wait, simply choose your table. I love that the restrooms are always stocked and clean. 
This time around, my father and I shared the machacado plate. Menu prices are reasonable. I give this whole experience a 3/5. Average. I love their hand made yellow corn tortillas. They always have good service. The ladies are friendly and kind.
I stopped by for lunch for the first time.  I ordered the beef enchilada lunch special.  Served volcano hot and very tasty.  The rice and beans served with the special we're pretty good too.
Great place with friendly people. Plenty of parking in the food comes out pretty fast
Food was pretty good.  And price is great. The service is great.
Love the authentic Mexican! Especially fried taco shells and super hot salsa. Queso is great too. A repeat in Austin

Giving five stars for a few key reasons: 1. It's a survivor in a period of heavy gentrification of Austin. 2. Great service 3. Huge portions of good food for a decent price. 

The place is divey, don't expect a nice environment. It's what makes it not feel like one of the new cookie cutter millennial magnet restaurants here now.

The food here is amazing and comes in large portion sizes. Service is always flawless and the whole place is warm and homey. This place reminds me of my grandma's house and they definitely respect their regulars. I love that they're open nights now and it's quickly becoming a chill hang out after a crazy night. Definitely an Austin classic.

Ridiculously over priced for a plain fajita taco six dollars no taste at all! Packaged tortillas I'd understand homemade, not only that but just meat no bell pepper or onions wow and they up charge to add lettuce and tomatoes. I'll never go back to pay for an over charged taco I think even at a food truck trailer I've had way better tacos.

Come here if you want amazing migas! Their biscuits are also very good, also some of the best coffee I have had from a restaurant. My husband and I enjoy coming here on the weekends for breakfast tacos to start our day, and we have had fast and friendly service every time we visit!
Quintessential Texas diner. Great breakfast. Great for late night as well. Most authentically-feeling “country” vibe I’ve found in Austin so far. A real treat!

The food at El Sunzal was great! Their menu has plenty of dishes to choose from! It is helpful if you are able to understand and speak a little Spanish :) Service was quick and food came out in a reasonable amount of time. We will definitely be back soon!

Overall food was good. The only thing that disappoint me was that the corn tamale qas super soggy and super sweet. I am not sure if is supposed to taste that way or have that texture though. But my husband  and i will be returning.

Went here for the first time on Sunday. Read all the great reviews and decided to give it a shot. Hole in the wall kinda joint but your their for the food not the decor. I decided to play it safe and go with the Popusas and Tamales both were delicious! Horchata is different from mexican horchatas I'm used to but it was really good. Will definitely come back to tryout more of their food.
Great food! I highly recommend their pupusas.
Great place. Great food, don't go too hungry it take a bit of time for the food to come out

Is the greatest place to have a home cooked breakfast. The service is friendly and fast and the management came over and talked to us, about our meal very friendly and nice. I cant wait to go back. If you haven't eaten at this place put it on your to do list! Keep up the great work !
AWESOME!I I was greeted warmly when I arrived. This made me feel welcome. It was very busy but a table was found. Chips and salsa were brought right away. Food was good you need to visit.
Beef Fajita is the real deal. Great service, food portions are good. Big place with lots of seats. Definitely a must go! Delicious! Thank you Juan in a Billion!!

Good food. Quick service. Welcoming staff, especially waitresses were great. Very lively place even though everyone at different tables were on their own business. Crowded perhaps due to popularity. Should better look a bit more tidy.

The Don Juan, enough said. There salsa is great. Has an addictive heat can't get enough. Enchiliadas rice and beans are great for lunch also. Nothing bad made here all with love and great customer service.

Highly recommend the Fish wrap (it's vegetarian of course)...YUMMY! Very nice customer service. Looks like a great place to order a vegan cake for a celebration. It's definitely a more relaxed environment, perfect for a lunch. Plenty of options for everyone ☺

They're really good I try to go there whenever I can. This resturant was actually the first vegan place I went to after moving to Austin. It's a really special place. They are always super nice whenever I go. And the food is always amazing.

I love Mr. Natural's food and bakery selection. Most of the people are nice and welcoming. However, I took my mom out for breakfast, and the service was awful. The owner is also quite rude and unwelcoming, and didnt do anything to make the situation better. 

The taco had hair in it, and we told them nicely, but all she said was "okay, I can't do anything. Sorry, I guess." 

I love their food, but this was unfortunate. I hope their customer service gets better and that they can compartmentalize their personal life and work.

I have been wanting to try Mr. Natural since I pass the two locations quite often. It was great because I was craving tamales and they have vegan options! There is so much to choose from and I loved it. Great hippie and free vibes in the restaurant. The dessert was also spectacular. They have vegan tres leches which was delish. The only reason I give them four stars is because of service and it could have been a little cleaner. But all in all, I want more cake.
Friendly and quick serving up healthy and delicious lunch options. I haven't tried their breakfast/dinner menu but I'd imagine it's great.

Small, hole in the wall, down-home southern BBQ spot, and the stretch of street it's on smells simply amazing! Pork ribs are out of this world! The owner, Brian, and his crew were very hospitable...lots of laughs...felt like family. If you're in the area, this BBQ is a must!

I moved away from the South a few years ago and it's been a struggle to find great BBQ. When I visited Austin, I was happy to find Sam's! Great brisket and a cozy atmosphere that felt like home. Definitely will be back the next time I'm in town.

Food is finger licking good! Bryan and his people are down to earth and where the place lacks in its aesthetics, it more than makes up for it in its down home hospitality. Everyone who comes through the door is treated to good eats with brite teeth. Love the brisket!
Recommended to me by a friend, this place was the exact experience we were looking for! Amazing ribs and mutton! Melty brisket and fall off the bones meat.
Several slices of Heaven! The Best Soul Food in Austin! Beans & tater salad only for sides. Open since 1958. If you're worried about the ambience, run on out to Bill Miller.
Friendly staff, nice food. We had a banquet for 7 people with a pile of beers. Loads of well prepared, tasty food and reasonably priced as well.
Really nice surroundings lovely friendly staff and great food.  Brilliant value for money.  Well worth a visit.
Fantastic food and friendly service. Only place that has good aromatic crispy duck. They make some great food.
Would give zero stars if possible. Food was terrible, and the service was even worse! Avoid like the plague.
Remember that You have to pay extra money for rice. Beef was... lets say "good" and the service really nice.

The food is good, very cheesy.  They used to be better.  They recently made the portions smaller.  

It needs diversity.  I always feel like the only colored guest at the restaurant. Feels weird.

I really enjoy the atmosphere here. It’s nice being able to get a margarita while you wait as well. The staff is always really nice and quick to help if you need a recommendation. My go to meal is the fajitas at this point. It’s always consistent and tasty.

The fajita tacos (one of each) are the BEST!! I only get this here. The enchiladas are pretty good too though but 4 star for me. The salsa is usually pretty spicy too so if you like it hot you will enjoy. Love this place but parking can be crazy.

Great place to take your ex-wife for lunch. Strong drinks. Great crispy taco and of course enchiladas. Good enough to concentrate on food instead of talking , or change the subject to food "oh, man, these beans" "good tortillas" that sort of thing.

I mean don't get divorced just to come here -- that seems excessive, but if it does happen. Spread your wings and bury the hatchet in a combo plate.
Great enchiladas! Good service. It gets pack at lunch tho. And good prices

Pretty good service.  Wanted a tad more flavor for my food.  Thought my chicken would have some grill flavor but tasted boiled instead.  I wasn't advised to pay on the way out. So I waited a whole for server to come take my payment then finally went and asked and was then made aware.

Great place, really good Margaritas. I was in town doing some work. My coworker suggested that we go there for dinner. I had the fajitas with beef. They were very good. Cecilia was our server, she was a delight and very knowledgeable on the menu. It was a truly amazing experience.

Cute, authentic vibe.

Great Salsa.

Nice waiter.

We ordered the Jardin appetizer and bean and cheese nachos.

So filling hit the spot

I eat here often.  The supreme breakfast burrito is awesome.  Everything, a full sausage patty, two strips bacon, eggs, potatoes, cheese, jalapeno, beans incl.  One is a full breakfast.  Yum.  Lunch and dinner just as good.  Decent prices, lots of delicious food, quick service.  Atmosphere is basic and not romantic.  Ceiling banners and neon beer signs.  A small, small bar in the front.
Excellent as always! Neighborhood Mexican food joint that pretty much every family goes to. Parking is sometimes hard to find but absolutely nothing wrong with the restaurant.
We've been to this restaurant numerous times over the past 20 years. Tonight our chef was awesome. He changed his cooking style, we had a great time. Give him a high 5.

Are big group in celebrating freedom of just the house what's one of our lovely friends not tonight where nice couple joined this. Now we have excellent service and the next one time we got everything we ordered I'm not sure who the couple next to us made mad but they certainly did not have the same experience we did I just find it important to note that for some reason. If it had been a reverse situation this would be a different review but personally my experience was five stars had I been them. I've been getting my money back.

Japanese hibachi is as much about the experience as the food and our cook did not disappoint.  In addition to the traditional fire show, he juggled flaming batons and shot fire into the air.  The food was excellent.  The service was good.  I felt like it was money well spent.
Pretty good. It has been quite some time since we have been there. I was to say at least five years. Much better than last time. Pretty busy for a Sunday.

My brother and I celebrated our birthday's at Kobe and they made it really special. Everything was great! The service, chef, food, and of course the birthday cake. I have finally found a Hibachi place that I love in Austin.

We love Manuel's Tavern. So iconic and such amazing history. A great watering hole with good food and service. Can't go wrong here. Ordered the club sandwich. Excellent! The steak fries were a bit cold and seemed quite old,  but I'm giving them a pass. They took great care of us today.
We had the gyro's w/ sweet potato tater tots. It was all very good. They also have a Kobe beef burger. The beer selection is good, kind staff and very cool welcoming atmosphere. Highly recommend.

Last week I attended a book event to meet an author and an entrepreneur.  Parking was available across the street from the restaurant. Upon arrival there was no signage as to where to go but I figured it out. Just before the event started I ordered a small bite because Because I ate earlier.  

My order of black beans and guacamole came out quickly and tasted fresh and delicious. From my review of the menu they have a variety of offerings for different diets.  

Staff were professional and friendly enough. 

I enjoyed my time there.
Great place overall. Very good for casual time with friends. Good for small event gatherings in The Nest. I've seen people host board game and tabletop have events here.

If they have the chicken pot pie... do it! Its loaded with lists of chicken and the "pie" on top can be lifted off so you can get the filling with just the right amount of crust. It was delicious, I hope it stays!!!!

Loved all of the accompanying dishes so you can create your own flavor combos. We got there just in time, around 6:30 before the mobs of people started to arrive around 7. The service was terrific, fast, warm smiles and the staff all had a collective effort. Be sure to say hi to the owner/host, he was the nicest guy and you can tell he took pride in his restaurant. We’ll definitely be back, but next time we’re trying the bbq table :) 

Also - be sure to get the chicken dumplings to start

It was good but I wouldn't say that it was stellar and I would come back. The food was average and the place is definitely historic. They need to up their game given there are many other fantastic korean good food options in Austin now. The place is a little hard to find as it is tucked away near a small Chinese Zen garden. The service was okay and took a while. We requested a few things but didn't get it on time. We had to ask the waiter multiple times. The interior was a little dim and bland. The tofu soup was really great though, not so sure about the cold noodles. It is worth a one time try but I can't fully recommend it as a too option, there are a lot other better ones.
We got Korean BBQ combo and everything was amazing! Great atmosphere, very helpful staff. Loved it!!
Have been coming here for ten years plus. Never a bad experience! Great atmosphere, and wonderful people.

Always great. They have cleaned, updated and renovated the place. They also performed a menu update after the previous owner, who was also the sushi chef, retired. No more sushi is a bummer. Also, my favorite dish consisting of stir fried baby octopus is gone. I was initially sad that my favorite dish was gone but it forced me to try something new and I was not let down! They were busy for lunch and all the diners seemed content. I will always come back.
