Delicious, authentic Vietnamese at affordable prices. Veggie options available. Fast, friendly service.
vietnamese food, yeah, super yummy. Stopped in on a Tuesday. Looking forward to a return trip. It has a good feel to it.
Amazing authentic food, great service. Can go wrong with an Austin classic!

This is a nice place in a strip mall.  I came later in the day for lunch and was surprised how busy they were.  This is. Good sign of how the food is.  The service was quick and friendly.  The food didn't take long to make and tasted good.  The menu is large with lots of options including vegetarian, so there is something for even the picky eaters.
Food was terrible. Service was rude. And they started cleaning while we were there, which emitted a terrible smell.

FireBowl does not disappoint!  I have been to  a couple of different locations, had lunch 4 or 5 times now.  Most recent visit, wasn't too hungry, asked about a lunch portion, cashier was very nice, since they did not have that she suggested an order from the kids menu. Ordered the chicken teriyaki and an egg roll. Food came out pretty quickly (it was busy lunchtime) and was exactly what we ordered, it was tasty, and hot. I would recommend adding lunch specials to the menu: a smaller portion of your meals with a side, like an egg roll or cup of soup.
Simply the best healthy option in the Arboretum area. I love the stir fry your way and miso soup.

When this location was run by the woman from a while back, it was fined tuned with enormous attention to detail!  Had always been a great place to pop by and take home or eat there. The past two times I’ve gone, it’s horrible. I ordered the orange chicken today with fried rice and it was a bowl of terrible mush. Disappointed. Last time, I thought it must have been a mistake, but it was even more disgusting today. Paid $20+ for two terrible bowls. I’m done!  No pun intended!
Quick and easy. Tasty and not too expensive. Good selection of dishes too. Staff is always friendly and helpful. A good place for a quick bite to eat. Outdoor seating available as well.
Good fast chinese food. Close to my office so good alternative to other fast food options.

Two words: COME HUNGRY! I was super impressed with the variety of their buffet. Excellent deal for the price. Their vegan options are outstanding! And the service was excellent. I’m sad it took me this long to discover this restaurant.

The lunch buffet is a decent deal. For ~$12.00 you get a nice variety of warm favorites. My issue is with the stickiness of the floor. I have been a handful of times as it close to my job, the floor varies from flypaper to vacuum sealed. Get your order to go (you can even do that with the buffet option.)

It is really good food along with good service. Thai curry is better than Thai Restaurants. This is the best Indian restaurant in the austin area. My kids don’t like Indian food much but they are always excited to eat at Zaika!!

Great service and delicious food! We went there for dinner and they didn't have thali option in their menu but on request made one for us. Have also tried their lunch buffet, amazing food. Tikki chat in buffet is the attraction. Very good for the price.
I had dinner at Zaika the other night. Everything we ordered was delicious and service was  great. I recommend this place and will definitely go back.

I enjoyed my first visit to this locally owned restaurant and tea room. It had been suggested that I get a reservation online through their website. The food was very well prepared and delicious. The service was attentive and respectful. Last but not least, that was the pot of tea I’ve had in a long while. It took me some time to read through all of the well explained tea list which is extensive. Great Job and I will be back!

I seriously love this place! The amount of tea available is just amazing. They also have really great food! I tend to go for Sunday brunch so I don't eat the lunch/dinner menu very often anymore, but everything they offer is delicious. One of my favorite things is the tempeh bacon. It is so delicious! I always order it when I go now.
A great experience for me and my God-daughter. How a 12 - year old native Texas girl got SO into English tea time - something I do not understand.  But, I am good with it.

I was very excited to try out this restaurant as I have dietary allergies to gluten and dairy. After ordering our food we did not see our waitress again for 50 minutes. We had to flag down another waitress and ask about our food. That waitress then brought us our food. At this point it had been an hour and we had not seen our waitress. Our food was cold and we were extremely hungry. When we asked why it took so long and complained about the cold food (again to another staff as our waitress was nowhere to be seen) we were told that it was such a long wait time because my dietary issues caused the food to take longer. This would be understandable if our waitress had come to update us, if the food had not been supper cold and if I had ordered something that needed a substitute. I got toast eggs and bacon with roasted potatoes. The toast was the only item that needed special precautions. 
During the 2 hours we were there we only saw our waitress twice. To take our order and to pick up the check. She was not even the person to bring us our check and apologize. 
It was overall an unpleasant experience and I am still hungry.
I give it 5 stars, my bank account gives it 1 because I want to buy ALL THE TEA!! It's all fairly priced, but I can't afford to buy the entire store.

You don't think much when you pass this wonderful little hole in the wall on the frontage road of 183. But as soon as you enter those doors you're greeted with the delicious aroma of fried goodness. I had the catfish nuggets and I've gotta hand it to them. Our one thing you cant do without is their shrimp sauce. It tastes like it might be homemade, but we didn't ask.

Friendly "Dive Bar" type of restaurant. Cold beer, good fried seafood and boiled crawfish. The french fries always disappoint but the catfish plates are great. Order a pitcher of beer, good value and they keep it cold in a bucket of ice water. The crawfish are a must order. The lunch special lasts until 3pm and is very good because it includes their gumbo, you will love it. I would give 5 stars for Pacific Star if it were not for the french fries.

Wow! Surprisingly good find. The catfish filet is large and very fresh. Fried shrimp are some of the best I’ve had. Hush puppies even, really good. Also the service was prompt and friendly, and the atmosphere is perfect. ... Also there was a cute, hopeful kitty outside that my gf was very excited about.
My wife and I recent went here on a Saturday afternoon.  The food was great and the staff was very friendly and helpful.  This is a great casual seafood restaurant!

Decent food but I would argue it costs about 25% more than it should. I had crawfish po'boy, oysters, and kid's catfish. Catfish was the only good value at $6.50. I am also annoyed at every place that offers styrofoam without asking. This is that place. But I loved seeing my kid's face when he tried an oyster for the first time. Service was fair.

One of few restaurants which provides French fries fried in peanut oil which gives unique taste. Their shake as well is yummy. Don't forget to grab some complimentary peanuts as well. They are fresh and fried salted nuts with shells. They have vegetarian options as well.

Cool joint like how the wrap the burgers in the foil so when you open cheese is melted. Fries are really good but get the cajun ones. A little expensive because everything is charged separately but worth trying and seeing if you like it yourself.
Food is always hot and fresh. Love the fries and hot dogs. I like all the burger options and the food is not too salty. Good stuff!
They were very nice and the food was good. This is one of the cleanest fast food spots in Austin even the bathroom is clean.
Good food and nice staff. Price of food is kind of high. Minimal decor and kind of looks  like a semi done.

Wally burger express is a burger and chicken joint in Northwest Austin.  They have a nice selection of good selection of hamburger, chicken, shacks and makes.  It has resemblance to am old DQ (because it used to be one). We had a hamburger and chicken.  The burger was good, nothing special, better than other places, definitely tasted fresh.  The chicken was good and in my opinion was better than the burger, but I would go back again and have either one.  I want to try the train wreck. Note that they do have a kids menu but I didn't see it in the boards.  You have to ask them, but if I be remember it was a burger, chicken fingers it grilled cheese with fries and drink.  The staff is friendly and the service is quick.  One caution was that the floor was slippery and I almost took a spill. I would say just be careful when you walk.  Great neighborhood place to grab a bite to eat.
I had the Train Wreck and it was delicious. Tried one of my daughters chicken fingers and it was pretty tasty. Fries were good too. Staff was super friendly. I'd go back.
Very good burgers, dogs and chicken... Tacos are good as well. My only complaint is they need to learn how to make a decent BLT. Deserts are good as well... Shakes, malts, etc.
Was pleasantly surprised the first time I was at Wally's. Everything was fresh and made to order. Delicious!
Great place to eat and hang out with friends! Good food and really kind staff. Remember if you don't want bad service don't be a bad costumer:)

The old Austin hip vibe runs deep here. Non-profit that shows local artists, including a lot of poster artists from the glory days of Armadillo, Soap Creek, and all the good old music venues of the 60's thru the 80's. There is a Memoriam Wall dedicated to past musicians and scenesters of the Golden Age of hip Austin.

The best and hopefully not the last location that honors true old Austin. 
So happy to hear that some of the musical items from the Threadgill's auction will find a home here! 
Adore this place & all of its staff.
♥️🙏 fun stop to pay tribute to those we all adore
Loved visiting with my husband and our friends. We enjoyed our time listening to Stephen Doster. We'll be back soon.
Strange Austin shrine-like ode toTexas musical artist. The headship Planet K is right next door as well as a mini postal station.

Waited about 40 minutes, which was fine for how busy they were.  The issue we had was big parties were being sat before smaller ones even though the smaller parties arrived first.  Our party was also skipped and when we asked about it we were told that our party was called when it was not. While asking about our table status we noticed our parties name was not marked off the list as being called either.  While dinning we were offer tortillas which were never delivered.  I debated between 2 and 3 stars but decided on 3 as we eat there often and have never experienced these issues before.
Amazing food! Authentic handmade tortillas and Menudo! My teenagers love the food here-even my vegetarian. Excellent service and clean facility. We will be back again 😁

I would have given this 5 stars because of the food, but our server was quite rude. When I ordered a drink and had a question about it, she was short with me. She was very friendly with my husband, though, of course. She always looked and spoke directly at him and basically ignored me. She wasn't flirting per se, just ignored me, which was very rude.
My husband went to the bathroom and while he was gone, she came back to say the beer he wanted wasn't available and asked what he'd like instead. Having never been there before, I said I didn't know and asked if she could check back when he returned. The look she gave me was the coldest look I've ever received at a restaurant. I'm sorry, but I'm supposed to order for my husband in a brand new place? WOW. 
She made a HUGE deal of it, too. When he came back, she actually told him that his own wife didn't know what he likes. Seriously, WOW.
I will not be back solely so we can avoid that server, who lost two customers by her behavior that day.

Went in this past weekend.
Food was good.
Seated quickly.
Santa the waitress was great-very easy going, down to earth, checked on us several times............made it a pleasant experience.........not like some other restaurants.  Thanks Santa!

They were super accommodating for our large party! Food came out fast & was awesome. Bartender was friendly. 
Google maps had the address so wrong so make sure you go West William cannon instead of East!

Best barbecue I've had in a long time. Between my brother, father and I, we tried just about every kind of meat on the menu. The brisket, sausage and pulled pork are so juicy and delicious that you don't even need to put barbecue sauce on it... Unless you like to live on the edge. This place was worth the trip to Austin and I plan on returning as soon as I'm back in town. I highly recommend this place.

First time coming here, prices are good and staff was good. However the food could have been better I got the one meat plate brisket, it was cold. My boyfriend ordered the three meat plate with ribs, sausage and smoked buffalo wings he stated It was okay the meat was cold also. The sides are okay nothing to fancy. Overall we have had better nice location .

Really nice, quiet place. Authentic, probably the same setup as 30-40 years ago. Down to earth BBQ. Brisket could have been bit juicier, potato salad great. Fries are very good! Atmosphere good, relaxed. Friendly staff. Great local beers.
Excellent service. Our waiter was extremely knowledgeable about the food ingredients. Incredibly important for someone with food allergies. He made our dining experience safe and worry free.

Laid back place, excellent food.  I had the ribs, beef, and pork with hush puppies and green beans.  Ribs were my favorite, meaty with a nice subtle smoke.  Brought our youngest who is not a barbecue fan and there was grilled cheese on the menu for him, a rare treat in a barbecue place.  Would recommend.

Not what it used to be! I used to love coming here in the mid 2000s for vermicelli, spring or summer rolls, and bubble tea. The place was very cute, with amazing, friendly service, extremely reasonable prices, and art from local artists for sale on the walls. The whole place was decorated with great, unpretentious taste, it went perfectly with the type of restaurant they were. I moved away and here I am visiting back about 12 yrs later, thinking it would be the same or better. Not only are the cute decor and atmosphere gone (the place was dark, the whole place has a grey-green lighting atmosphere that doesn't feel very inviting), the menu is completely different, the pho I had was nothing to write home about, the prices do not reflect the quality of the food  (too high), but the worst part of it all was the waiter. When we were ordering drinks, I asked for jasmine bubble tea, and he told me immediately that they had no bubble tea and that they had never served it. I told him that they used to serve different types back in the day and he started arguing about how I was wrong, because they had never, ever served bubble tea. This waiter had an attitude the rest of the time he was waiting on us. I won't go back whenever I'm back in Austin, I am sure there are other newer and better places for vermicelli, rolls and bubble tea in Austin.

Best pho I've tasted in Austin... so far. Establishment is small and gets really crowded during lunch hours, parking is limited as it is shared with other busy businesses. staff is always great and food delicious.
My favorite Vietnamese food in town. Love the casual atmosphere and great staff! 5 stars y'all!

Great service! Food was literally ready in less than 10 minutes. Great ambience. Fast, small,clean, casual. The waiter knew everything about the menu and helped me find something delicious. Loved it! I got the veggie tofu fried rice. Fresh, fragrant and delicious! Def coming back.
Vietnamese food at this location - delicious. Came here on a Friday I think. Food is like a place in Baltimore I loved.

Best Breakfast Tacos in Austin!!
Taco Express is the best - no doubt about it. Their breakfast is awesome, that I've never made it to the lunch menu no matter what time of day I go there. They serve breakfast all day! Perfect for those weekend days that you wake up later than normal. They have a different vibe in their dining room, it's very Austin. Great food and service. The salsa is terrific also. Their tacos are super tasty, not overly greasy and they give you a lot inside their tacos, they are pretty full. Their location is fairly easy to get to and they take phone orders and are super speedy!

Maria's is an Austin classic. With a menu that will satisfy any diet or craving. Their in house corn tortillas are the best I've ever had. They are dog friendly and have amazing music on Sundays. If you're in Austin, and you want good tacos hit up Maria's.

The food here was so delicious. Everything was made fresh to order. Food was ready quickly and people were cleaning the entire time we were there. Great variety of food choices. Lots of personality. There was outdoor seating as well as an upstairs lounge. I would love to visit again the next time I'm in town.

Pretty cool place. Went to play Big Boobied Bingo there one Tuesday night and had a good time. Their queso is alright, i think everything there is pretty much frozen then heated. Margaritas was good though. Not too sure about their food yet.

Went for Big Boobie Bingo while visiting Austin - had a BLAST! The hosts were hysterical and kept us laughing for 3 hours. We had the chips and queso (delicious), and our friends had tacos - they looked really good. The drinks (margaritas, full bar, soda, etc) were hand crafted and reasonably priced. Get there early for a good seat.

I don't enjoy that they always have a wait. That being said, I do enjoy the food. It isn't the best Mexican cuisine I've ever had, but it's pretty good. I wish the tortillas were made fresh. I also think they salsa is a tad too hot for a general table salsa. The fajitas are yummy.

I am sure that there are plenty of reviews that mention the Bob. So I'm not going to go into it. What you really want here are the Red Snapper fish tacos with sale and rice. Super good.

The grilled old fashion tacos and pastor tacos are some of the best tacos you can find in Austin - and I have had them all.

Don't make a rookie mistake and walk out without a praline.

My salad was incredible! Colorful and delicious, full of fresh crunchy vegetables and perfectly seasoned chicken! The chipotle ranch dressing was good too but I added some salsa as well to spice it up a little more. The waitress, Marissa (I believe), was very attentive and incredibly friendly! Highly recommend! ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐

*UPDATE*

I will no longer be coming to this establishment.
In the last 9 months, I can say I have eaten here at least 40 times. My experience today with my waitress has left a really bad taste in my mouth. She was abruptly rude from the moment we sat down to even when we ordered an appetizer. Her annoyed face expression when we asked for a side of jalapeños to go along with the guacamole set the tone. I figured she may have had a busy day and dropped it and finished with ordering drinks and she walked away. A minute later she came back asking for my ID and I gladly showed it to her. Her rude demeanor immediately made me lose my appetite. No desire to order from this and or ever step back into this restaurant. 

Where do I start!? This happens to be my new favorite Mexican restaurant in Texas. The service, atmosphere, and food are top notch.
I'm finding myself here at least twice a week!
1) it's down the street from me 2) the drinks and fajitas are the best.
My first visit wasn't the greatest, the waitress was overwhelmed...but still didn't stop me from coming back. Good thing I did! It's been fantastic service since. I highly recommend this place if you want amazing food and good customer service.
It's been hot out, but sitting in the back outdoor area is fantastic. Don't forget to try their top shelf margarita... It's amazing!
You won't regret it.

Delicious food!! Very easy to find from Google directions! Plenty parking,  even valet for a fee.  The restaurant has been at least 25 years. Please be ready for a wait of 30 min to an hour or more. You must check in at hostess desk and give your name and cell phone number to be text upon table ready. Not too many seats, be prepared to stand. Staff is very friendly and ready to accommodate!! A little loud, but fun environment! Indoor, outdoor with heat and patio seating. Bar is open to serve you drinks while waiting,  that's a good thing! Decor is customary to culture.  Go on an empty stomach,  portion are good! Check it for yourself! 💯👍

Good stuff! I'm from out of town, so I just stopped by Sandy's on a whim. I knew going in that it was just going to be like a cheap, drive-in burger joint, and that's exactly what it is and that's okay! The food won't blow your mind, but it's exactly the comfort food you want. It tastes good, it's cheap, and it puts a smile on your face. They've also got some really good combo deals to check out. Sandy's is definitely worth a stop!
Sandy's is still good. Never great, but doing well with what they do. Weekly combo special makes the trip worth it. Always a nice alternative to other fast food.
A once a year treat but since I was a kid I'm in my thirties now still follow the tradition. No crazy names for burgers no weird shakes simply the Best.
Oh man! I'm from Austin so I've been eating Sandy's for years and years. Awesome burgers creamy soft serve ice cream. truly and Austin original... Saturday special is the bomb

Just swung through for the frozen custard which tasted more like soft serve. Very good even if their drive-through intercom sucks. Would definitely go back, I'm surprised I never stopped in the many years I lived in Austin

This Cafe is a great brunch location and stays pretty busy on the weekend. We called an hour ahead and secured our spot. Great, quick service. Food came out fast considering how busy they were. Place is clean though it could use a little brighter color. Nothing negative about the place.

Lively atmosphere, good service and good quality food. The burger was good, if a little rich for my taste. But even though they were busy, I didn't wait long for anything and the waitress was attentive and apologetic for the wait I did have. A little thing but a huge attention to detail was the butter. It was soft, seasoned, and whipped, easily spread on the warm bread unlike a hard rock you have to crack with an ice pick like other places.

Tasty Americana fare with a Southern flair. Large selection of beers on tap. Beers and apps are half off during happy hour. Both apps and entrees were quite delicious. Servers were attentive. Good people watching too if you get a table by the window!

Vibrant place, specially for brunch. There's usually a wait but totally worth it. Service is good but take into consideration the amount of customers they are tending. This is not a high class place but a down to earth goodness sort of restaurant.

Tight quarters and a bit of a wait for brunch. We called in beforehand as recommended on the site got their around 11:30 and had a 45 min wait which really wasn't bad. Without calling ahead that wait was 1.5 to 2 hours. Food was pretty good. Their cornbread is delicious and apparently gluten free. The carrot cake french toast was good as well. It was a lot of food and definitely requires a sweet tooth. They had some good gluten free options for their brunch entrees as well. Coffee was good. It's a tight spot though. We were close to the kitchen and had a constant stream of trays coming by. Service was friendly and fast.
Awesome place to find the “original” Austin.  Take your time and look at the murals.  Be sure to stop by on the weekends for the artists market!!! Support local businesses and Keep Austin Weird!!

It's a nice spot with historical story. This place used to be the center spot of hang out for the "drag rats" who where homeless youngsters dressed in raggedy punk rock style clothes.
This place is now used for the Artist's Market which are individual artisans selling their awesome works, from jewelry to bags, and other accessories.

There are beautiful murals there painted by austinite artists, as well as some graffitis on the walls. The main entrance to the University of Texas is right across from it.

This spot is like a little park, unofficially, and is a nice spot to visit and take some pictures.

This was the perfect place for our son's Rehearsal Dinner!  The venue is beautiful, educational and spacious.  We were able to rehearse outside, (huge yard, and many different approaches to choose from)and then hold the dinner for 40 inside their amazing museum.  Our Event Manager, Andrea Perry, was so wonderful to work with; she is organized, thinks on her feet,  (we had a last minute problem with the bartender we hired to cater - she handled it) and was my favorite vendor to work with out of all the companies hired to help with the wedding.  Go here!  It's affordable, is for a great non-profit cause, and beautiful.

A great place to visit, it provides a glimpse of Austin's wonderful history. So many structures are being forgotten and left to ruin. 

At various times of month there could be a special presentation.  This month was quilts of the past and folk painting.  Both great to see.

Can make an arrangement for a personal tour through history.

Caught it on a free day and I'm glad we did as it was worth visiting at that price. Parking is limited so going on Sunday saved some walking. This is, of course, a love affair with LBJ, but there was a lot to love. A truly great man, and this is an homage to him. 
But even if you don't like LBJ, the historical artifacts are mind-boggling. 

So many original documents and items, that it is really an education. Like many museums, if you really want to read everything, it would take you an entire day. This eclectic outdoor market has remained in the same place with the same standard (local artists & craftspeople selling their own hand-made wares) since the 1970's. There are very few places left in Austin that can claim that lineage. The wide variety of artisans, their work and the price ranges ensure there's something for just about anyone at the 23rd Street Artists Market. I can't think of a place to find a more authentic Austin souvenir than strolling through. My favorite thing about 23rd Street is that it's never the same place twice (great photo ops & eateries all around too). Support your local artists and help Keep Austin Austin.
